data.description: This delightful two-story home offers a host of advantages, highlighted by its superb location, recent roof replacement, and upgraded rain gutters. Step inside to discover the charm of dark laminate wood flooring in both the living room and master bedroom on the main floor, complemented by fresh lighting throughout. The well-appointed kitchen boasts tile flooring, granite countertops, an island, maple cabinetry, an eat-in area, stainless steel appliances, and a bar counter overlooking the living room. Convenience is key with a first-floor master bedroom, while the upper level accommodates three additional bedrooms and a bathroom. The laundry closet is thoughtfully situated on the main floor.Outside, the house showcases a beautifully landscaped front yard and enjoys a sense ofseclusion adjacent to wetlands. The fully fenced backyard is complete with a screen porch and patio, offering an ideal setting for outdoor living and grilling. Storage options abound, with a walk-in attic space, a 1-car garage, and a storage unit in the back. Additional perks include access to amenities such as a pool and play parks. Positioned in close proximity to I-526, Mt. Pleasant, and N. Charleston, this residence seamlessly combines comfort and convenience.
